cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.CV

The paper presents a black-box attack against machine learning classifiers, specifically those based on API call sequences. This suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of computer security (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), software engineering (cs.SE), or computer vision (cs.CV). However, given the focus on attacking classifiers and generating adversarial examples, cs.CR and cs.LG are the most likely categories. The use of recurrent neural networks and deep neural networks also supports the inclusion of cs.AI. The discussion of defense mechanisms and the implementation of a software framework for recrafting malware binaries suggest a potential fit with cs.SE. Finally, while there is no explicit mention of computer vision, the use of printable strings as additional features could potentially relate to image processing and thus justify the inclusion of cs.CV as a less likely category.
